{%- comment -%}
  GPSR Safety Block — storefront Liquid block.

  Data source: three app-owned product metafields written by the backend
  (service/shopify_metafield.go) after apply-ruleset, set-override, or
  needs_review classification. All three metafields share the "$app"
  GraphQL namespace, which maps to "app" in Liquid.

  Terminal-state render contract (F7-storefront-contract.md §§):
    gpsr_status == "ok"       → render full block (entity + warnings)
    gpsr_status == "override" → render full block (override data IS the compliance data)
    gpsr_status == "needs_review" → render NOTHING (empty/hidden container)
    gpsr_status absent / blank    → render NOTHING (same as needs_review)

  NEVER render partial data or a "pending" placeholder for non-ok states.

  XSS contract (spec §5):
    - Every {{ output }} of metafield/setting data uses the escape filter (defense-in-depth).
    - Liquid auto-escapes {{ }} output; the escape filter is mandatory per spec and
      verified by the ai-security-review gate (grep on blocks/*.liquid).
    - Unescaped output filters are prohibited. No JavaScript in this block (MVP).
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- comment -%}
  App-owned metafields use the reserved namespace "$app" (see Shopify "Reserved
  prefixes for metafields in theme app extensions"). They MUST be accessed with
  the bracket syntax product.metafields["$app"].<key> — the dotted form
  product.metafields.app.<key> resolves to a literal "app" namespace (empty) and
  the block would always render blank.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign gpsr_status = product.metafields["$app"].gpsr_status.value -%}

{%- if gpsr_status == "ok" or gpsr_status == "override" -%}

  {%- assign gpsr_entity   = product.metafields["$app"].gpsr_entity_json.value -%}
  {%- assign gpsr_warnings = product.metafields["$app"].gpsr_warnings_json.value -%}

  <div class="gpsr-safety-block" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>

    {%- if block.settings.heading != blank -%}
      <h2 class="gpsr-safety-block__heading">
        {{- block.settings.heading | escape -}}
      </h2>
    {%- endif -%}

    {%- if block.settings.show_entity and gpsr_entity != blank -%}
      <div class="gpsr-safety-block__entity">
        {%- if gpsr_entity.name != blank -%}
          <p class="gpsr-safety-block__entity-name">
            {{- gpsr_entity.name | escape -}}
          </p>
        {%- endif -%}
        {%- if gpsr_entity.address != blank -%}
          <p class="gpsr-safety-block__entity-address">
            {{- gpsr_entity.address | escape -}}
          </p>
        {%- endif -%}
        {%- if gpsr_entity.role != blank -%}
          <p class="gpsr-safety-block__entity-role">
            {{- gpsr_entity.role | escape -}}
          </p>
        {%- endif -%}
      </div>
    {%- endif -%}

    {%- if block.settings.show_warnings and gpsr_warnings != blank and gpsr_warnings.size > 0 -%}
      <ul class="gpsr-safety-block__warnings">
        {%- for warning_text in gpsr_warnings -%}
          {%- if warning_text != blank -%}
            <li class="gpsr-safety-block__warning">
              {{- warning_text | escape -}}
            </li>
          {%- endif -%}
        {%- endfor -%}
      </ul>
    {%- endif -%}

  </div>

{%- endif -%}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "GPSR Safety Block",
  "target": "section",
  "enabled_on": {
    "templates": ["product"]
  },
  "stylesheet": "safety-block.css",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "heading",
      "label": "Section heading",
      "default": "Product Safety Information",
      "info": "Displayed above the responsible operator and safety warnings on the product page."
    },
    {
      "type": "checkbox",
      "id": "show_entity",
      "label": "Show responsible operator",
      "default": true,
      "info": "Displays the economic operator name, address, and role required by EU GPSR."
    },
    {
      "type": "checkbox",
      "id": "show_warnings",
      "label": "Show safety warnings",
      "default": true,
      "info": "Displays the product-specific safety warnings assigned by the GPSR app."
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
